title: Teeny Tiny Pecan Pies
description:
The correct pronunciation of "pecan" may be up for debate, but Trader Joe's Teeny Tiny Pecan Pies are an 
undeniably delicious and endearing dessert. Like our Teeny Tiny Apple Pies [sku 77455], this nutty variety is 
made for us in Canada, with each pie measuring about three inches in diameter. A sweet brown sugar & Pecan 
filling is nestled in a flaky, buttery crust, topped with an (ironically named) Junior Mammoth pecan half, 
and baked until golden brown. Delightfully gooey with a soft bite, these petite pastries will satisfy Pecan Pie 
cravings without the commitment to a full-size pie. 

Teeny Tiny Pecan Pies are excellent right out of the box, and are especially delectable when heated in the 
oven, microwave, or air fryer, according to package directions. If you've got a second to spare, top yours with 
a flourish of Light Whipped Cream [sku 22791], or a teeny tiny scoop of French Vanilla Ice Cream [sku 78576]. 
With four pies per box, you can always enjoy them with friends and freshly-brewed cups of Joe Medium Roast 
Ground Coffee [sku 56332]. You'll find Teeny Tiny Pecan Pies in the bakery section, only during the holidays-
pick up a box while supplies last!

Teeny Tiny Pecan Pies

title: Dinner Rolls
description:
Hard, stale bread certainly has a place at the dinner table in the form of salad croutons and poultry stuffing. 
When it comes to rolls, however, it's quite...sacrolligious. And yet, dry Dinner Rolls seem to prevail in grocery 
stores across the land. Not at Trader Joe's, though-we say "no" to roll mediocrity with our soft and moist 
Dinner Rolls.

Bite into one of these pull-apart Rolls, and you'll notice that they're incredibly moist compared to other store-
bought options. The secret? Potato flour! This spudsy superstar attracts and holds water better than other 
flours, so we add a bit of it to give Trader Joe's Dinner Rolls their especially soft texture. A touch of sugar lends 
subtle sweetness, making for craveable rolls that'll have you questioning if it's worth saving room for dinner. 

Dinner Rolls are most delicious when warmed in the oven for 3-5 minutes at 400°F. Place them in a basket 
atop holiday dinner tables and serve with Salted Butter Quarters [sku 06252], or tangy Cultured Salted Butter 
[sku 53720], if you're feeling fancy. They also excel as slider buns, and as carb companions to soup and salad 
dinners. You'll find Dinner Rolls in the bakery section through the holiday season, while supplies last. 

Dinner Rolls
tags: ["Effortless Entertaining","Fall Faves","Family Style","Picnic","Put An Egg On It","Time-pressed"]

title: Organic Fig & Honey Batard
description:
Nothing says French bread like the iconic baguette seen in many a market tote bag. But what about this svelte 
bread's more rotund presentation: batard? We'd wager this lesser-known shape is equally delicious, especially 
when in the form of Trader Joe's savory-sweet Organic Fig & Honey Batard.

This Batard comes to us from a French bakery that specializes in Organic, artisanal bread. They mix dried 
Figs and Honey into traditional French bread dough for a bit of sweetness and pops of subtle fruit flavor. The 
dough is then shaped into an oblong loaf and baked until light golden brown. Soft and airy on the inside, it's 
best enjoyed after warming and crisping in the oven, according to package directions.

The sweetness of Organic Fig & Honey Batard makes it delightful on its own, and a wonderful match for 
strong and salty flavors. Slice to your desired thickness and keep it simple with a spread of Cultured Salted 
Butter [sku 53720], or take things up a notch with slices of Société Roquefort [sku 89767] and a glass of Joseph 
Händler Riesling [sku 99461]. You'll find Organic Fig & Honey Batard in the bakery section through the 
holiday season-pick up yours while supplies last!

Organic Fig & Honey Batard
tags: ["Alfresco Dining","Date Night","Effortless Entertaining","Feeling Fancy","Pair With Wine"]

title: Sourdough Boules
description:
Trader Joe's has all the shapes in our bakery section: circular bagels; slender baguettes; flat-breads... We thought 
it was about time we got around to boules. Trader Joe's Sourdough Boules not only bring their unique ball 
shape, but they also bring delicious bread that rises to so many excellent eating occasions.

Our Boules are made with a wild yeast Sourdough starter and long fermentation, to build a light, airy crumb-
and to yield the slightly nutty, slightly tangy taste that one expects from sourdough. The seven-ounce, round 
loaves-about five inches in diameter by three inches tall-are baked until the crust is golden brown and 
delightfully chewy, with a satisfying, open crumb.

All these traits mean Trader Joe's Sourdough Boules are great sliced and toasted for breakfast with TJ's 
Cultured Salted Butter [sku 53720] and Organic Reduced Sugar Strawberry Preserves [sku 95227]. For lunch, try 
some topped with a Teeny Tiny Avocado [sku 75444]. Speaking of shapes, you can cut a Boule into cubes and 
toast them for the best croutons you've ever had on your salad! And if soup is on the menu, why not turn your 
Boule in to a bowl, then fill it with TJ's New England Clam Chowder [sku 55218]. However you choose to enjoy 
it, you're guaranteed to have a Boule!

Sourdough Boules

title: Sea Salt Chocolate Chunk Cookies
description:
Imagine sinking your teeth into the perfect cookie: first, there's the initial toothsome resistance of the crisp 
outer layer, and the sweet aromas of butter and vanilla. Then, that resistance gives way to the soft, chewy 
interior and full flavors of semisweet chocolate, brown sugar, and sea salt. Imagine the chocolate and soft 
cookie melting in your mouth, expressing all kinds of sweet and savory flavors as you wash it down with a 
chilled glass of milk (or non-dairy beverage). Now, what if we told you that this exact experience is readily 
available at your neighborhood Trader Joe's? Imagine no more: we present to you The Sea Salt Chocolate 
Chunk Cookie.
 
Now made using an updated recipe that results in an even softer, even fresher-feeling texture, each box contains 
six Sea Salt Chocolate Chunk Cookies that are big in both size and flavor. In fact, they're just about the perfect 
size and shape for making delicious cookie ice cream sandwiches, and the bits of coarse, crunchy Sea Salt 
interact wonderfully with a scoop of French Vanilla Ice Cream [sku 78576]. That said, if you're more in the 
mood for a simpler, solo Cookie experience, try warming one up in the microwave for a few seconds just prior 
to enjoying.

Sea Salt Chocolate Chunk Cookies

title: Gluten Free Chocolate Chunk Cookies
description:
Imagine sinking your teeth into the perfect chocolate chip cookie. First, there's the initial resistance of the 
cookie's crisp outer layer. Then, just as that resistance gives way to the cookie's soft, chewy interior, you're hit 
with a symphony of buttery, brown-sugary, and, of course, chocolatey flavor. "It's pitch-perfect!" You exclaim. 
"We agree," we respond, "and it's gluten free." Shocked, you reach for the box, and there it is, plain as day: 
Trader Joe's Gluten Free Chocolate Chunk Cookies with Sea Salt. Well, I'll be darned...

Now made using an updated recipe that results in an even softer, even fresher-feeling texture, these Gluten 
Free Chocolate Chunk Cookies are a true achievement in gluten free baking. Each box contains six Cookies 
made with a blend of oat flour, rice flour, tapioca starch, brown sugar, and plenty of butter. The real scene-
stealers, however, are the rich, semi-sweet Chocolate Chunks throughout and the coarse Sea Salt sprinkled on 
top. Together, they offer up an effortless harmony of sweet and salty-it's the kind of Cookie confluence that'll 
bring you back for another bite. And another. And another-thank goodness we're selling them six to a box. 
You'll find them in our bakery section.

Gluten Free Chocolate Chunk Cookies
with Sea Salt

title: Gluten Free Baguette
description:
In the world of bread, baguettes are serious business. In fact, the baguette has been deemed such an iconic part 
of France's culinary history, that the tradition of baguette-making was recently added to UNESCO's Intangible 
Cultural Heritage Lists, placing it in the same global esteem as Flamenco dance, Kabuki theatre, and yoga. With 
such a significant cultural presence, we thought it would be a shame if folks who don't eat gluten missed out on 
all the fun, which is why we're happy to introduce Trader Joe's Gluten Free Baguette to our bakery sections.

Made with a mix of tapioca starch and oat flour, as well as a bit of gluten free sourdough starter to give every 
bite a delightfully tangy, sourdough tinge, Trader Joe's Gluten Free Baguette strikes an artful balance between 
artisanal and rustic. We find it's best when warmed in an oven at 400°F for about ten minutes, after which its 
crust becomes particularly crisp, and the whole Baguette is ready for any situation that calls for a baguette. It 
makes an especially hearty sandwich bread (gluten-free bánh mì, anyone?), it makes great crostini when sliced 
into rounds and toasted, and can even just be torn or sliced into hunks and dipped with your favorite olive oil.

Gluten Free Baguette
tags: ["Alfresco Dining","Cheese Board","Cut The Mustard","Effortless Entertaining","Pair With Wine","Put An Egg On It"]

title: Pumpkin Loaf
description:
Need something to help you step into the fall spirit? It's easy-all you need is Trader Joe's Pumpkin Loaf! 
It starts, unsurprisingly, with Pumpkin purée, which gives the wheat flour-based Loaf an incredibly moist 
and not too dense crumb. A parade of spices-cinnamon, nutmeg, allspice, ginger, and cloves, to be exact-
intermingle with notes of vanilla to create the classic spice profile one would expect to find in autumnally-
inspired baked goods. Topping it off is a crowning layer of crunchy sugar and a generous dusting of aromatic, 
fall-forward spices, ensuring every bite is is imbued with the spirit of the season.
 
Almost as delightful as the Pumpkin Loaf itself is its open-and-enjoy nature-all you have to do is slice and 
serve, perhaps alongside a glass of iced Pumpkin Spice Flavored Cold Brew Concentrate Coffee [sku 79207] 
or a hot cup of Colombia Supremo Coffee [sku 50976]. If you've got a bit more time on your hands, you might 
toast a slice and  drizzle with Creamy Salted Almond Butter [sku 51436] and Pumpkin Butter [sku 06372]. 
Gilding the lily? Maybe. Scrumptiously satisfying? You bet! 

If all you need is Loaf, then make haste-these Pumpkin Loaves are limited to the fall season!

Pumpkin Loaf

title: Pumpkin Spice Mini Sheet Cake
description:
It's no secret that our customers love the airy cake and decadent frosting that make up our Mini Sheet Cakes. 
Their smaller format and convenient reclosable lid (in addition to their aforementioned deliciousness) have 
cemented our collective belief that cake is not just for birthdays, but worthy of enjoyment all year long, in myriad 
flavors. 

Cake¿ er, case in point: Trader Joe's Pumpkin Spice Mini Sheet Cake. You'll fall for the moist, spongy crumb, 
flavored by pumpkin purée and warm spices, including cinnamon, nutmeg, and ginger. A rich, cream-cheese 
frosting is piped on top, lending an upscale bakery vibe and providing a classic flavor-pairing for the Pumpkin 
Spice profile.

Add some candles and deliver to your friends who have autumn birthdays. Serve at the conclusion of a casual fall 
meal along with freshly brewed TJ's Pumpkin Spice Coffee [sku 97234]. Or, cut it into bite-sized pieces, and serve it 
to yourself throughout the day-whenever you're walking by the kitchen. This Cake doesn't require refrigeration, 
so you can store it on the counter for quick & easy access!

Pumpkin Spice Mini Sheet Cake

title: Dark Chocolate Ganache Mini Sheet Cake
description:
Cake is too often relegated to special occasions. That's partially because it takes too much time and effort to bake 
one for 'no particular reason.' Of course, premade cakes are always an option, but what's typically available for 
purchase is either too fancy (and expensive) for everyday enjoyment, or just poor quality. Trader Joe's Dark 
Chocolate Ganache Mini Sheet Cake is the yummy solution for people who crave quality cake-even when it's 
nobody's birthday.

This cake is "Mini"-about 6 servings. It's a single layer of moist, flavorful chocolate cake made with buttermilk 
for extra richness. A delicious Dark Chocolate Ganache icing (made with butter, cream, & cream cheese) is 
generously spread on top, adding a decadent touch to this simple cake. Our Mini Sheet Cake is casual and 
small enough that your family can enjoy it as a special treat anytime. It's also fancy and big enough to serve at 
an intimate dinner party. (And, you can always add candles and an icing-message on top for a mini-birthday 
celebration.) No need to refrigerate-the re-closeable, clear-top lid helps to keep it fresh for up to six days. 

So, don't wait until it's someone's birthday before you enjoy your next slice of cake. Each 18-ounce Trader Joe's 
Dark Chocolate Ganache Mini Sheet Cake is just $4.49-the perfect price and the perfect size to justify a 
celebration everyday! You'll find it on our bakery tables.
tags: ["Date Night","Effortless Entertaining","Family Style","Stuff of Dreams","Treat Yourself"]

title: Sliced Seedy Multigrain Bread
description:
They say that good things come in threes; Trader Joe's Seedy Multigrain Loaf proves they also come in sevens! 
With a kitchen-sink blend of seven seeds and grains, each slice ups the textural ante for toast and sandwiches. 

Sunflower kernels and flax & sesame seeds are gently roasted to amplify their nutty flavor before uniting with 
hulled millet and barley, rye, and oat flakes. The seeds and grains are then sprinkled on wheat flour dough, and 
the resulting Loaf-to-be undergoes a low and slow fermentation process that transforms it into a chewy, hearty, 
and texturally intriguing bread befitting the entire toast-to-sandwich spectrum.

Conveniently pre-sliced, Seedy Multigrain Loaf lets you skip the crumby fractions and zero in on culinary 
calculations. Organic Apricot Preserves [sku 75418] + Supreme Brie [sku 66562] + Oven Roasted Turkey Breast 
[sku 81594] = sophisticated weekday sandwiches. Mashed avocado + Nori Komi Furikake [sku 60255] + jammy 
egg halves = Japanese-inspired toast. Or, simplify the equation with just a pat of Cultured Salted Butter [sku 
53720] on a toasted slice or two. The options are infinite!

Seedy Multigrain Loaf

title: Brioche Style Liège Waffles
description:
Did you know there is more than one kind of Belgian waffle? Breakfast eaters most often enjoy Brussels-style 
waffles, which are fairly large and rectangular with light, airy insides, and an exterior crunch-similar to Trader 
Joe's Belgian Waffles [sku 96967]. But another Belgian waffle has been gaining global fans in recent years, and it 
hails from the city of Liège. Trader Joe's Brioche Style Liège Waffles follow in this tradition.

Made for us in Belgium, our Liège Waffle dough not only includes flour, yeast, water, and salt-but also 
incorporates cultured butter, pearl sugar, and egg. This recipe yields a denser Waffle with buttery, brioche-like 
flavor. Compared to Brussels-style waffles, these are smaller and roundish, with rustic, uneven edges. And 
there's a distinct crunch that comes from the bits of sugar strewn throughout these handheld batter-cakes.

Waffle lovers will be enamored by the fact that Trader Joe's Brioche Liège Waffles can be enjoyed at room 
temperature, no toasting required. Enjoy them for an afternoon snack, as many Europeans do. Or grab one on 
your way out the door in the morning for a quick, satisfying breakfast. Of course, you can still opt to top them 
with whatever you like. Try serving some Brioche Style Liège Waffles after dinner with a sprinkle of powdered 
sugar, or a scoop of French Vanilla Ice Cream [sku 45883]. You'll find Trader Joe's Brioche Style Liège Waffles 
on the shelves in our bakery section, every day.

Brioche Style Liège Waffles with Pearl Sugar

title: Gluten Free Blueberry Muffins
description:
If baking is a science, then Trader Joe's Gluten Free Muffins are modern marvels beloved by gluten free eaters 
and gluten enthusiasts alike. The newest member of the lineup is sweet, fruity, and beautifully blue-that's 
right, Gluten Free Blueberry Muffins are in the Bakery section for a limited time!

Let's start from the (muffin) top. These wheatless wonders mimic gluten's texture building properties thanks 
to a blend of cornstarch, tapioca starch, oat flour, and not one, but three types of rice flour. We combine this 
magical mixture with sour cream, a hint of natural vanilla flavor, and a smidge of lemon oil for a moist, tangy, 
and aromatic cake base that rivals its glutenous counterparts. 

There are no blueberry muffins without blueberries, and our Gluten Free Blueberry Muffins are chock full 
of 'em. Baking brings the berries to their sweetest, fruitiest, and bluest form for muffins that taste as vibrant 
as they look. Coarse sugar and oat streusel top off each muffin top with a bit of crunch and a boost of butter. 

Gluten Free Blueberry Muffins make for a sweet breakfast alongside smooth, medium roast coffee like Fair 
Trade Organic Breakfast Blend [sku 74368]. For a lemony twist, gently warm in the microwave or toaster oven 
and slather with Authentic Lemon Curd [sku 07850].

Gluten Free 
Blueberry Muffins

title: Carrot Mini Sheet Cake
description:
Whose idea was it to put carrot in a cake anyway? In Medieval Europe, sugar was so inaccessible that the 
populace had to get creative with satisfying its sweet tooth. Abundant in quantity and sufficiently sweet, carrots 
got the job done-and then some. Not only did they contribute understated sweetness; they also increassed 
moisture content to keep desserts fluffy. Taking notes from both Medieval masses and grandmas of yore, 
Trader Joe's festively spiced Carrot Mini Sheet Cake evokes nostalgia with every bite. 

Shredded carrots and warm spices are baked together in a sweet and nutty base. Speaking of nuts, walnuts lend 
just enough bite to contrast the cake's moist and tender crumb. As with our mainstay Mini Sheet Cakes, cream 
cheese icing ribbons top off each slice with a tinge of tanginess and creamy texture. 

There's no baking or heating necessary for this scrumptious cake. Go right ahead and serve after weeknight 
dinners, add candles for birthday celebrations, or gift a whole sheet to the carrot cake lover in your life. 

Carrot Mini Sheet Cake is available in our bakery section for a limited time, so make haste to your neighborhood 
Trader Joe's!

Carrot Mini Sheet Cake

title: Flour Tortillas
description:
When it comes to making bold & ¿ avorful, burritos, captivatingly melty quesadillas, or rich and tasty wraps, it's 
important to have a good ¿ our tortilla at the ready. ¿ at's why we proudly o¿ er Trader Joe's Flour Tortillas in 
our bakery section. ¿ ey're cra¿ ed for us by a renowned, family-owned tortilla maker in Southern California, 
who's been making tortillas for Trader Joe's for more than 35 years. At about ten inches in diameter, these so¿  
and pliable Flour Tortillas are the ideal size for building burritos-but that's hardly where we'd stop.

Our Flour Tortillas are superb for serving with a plate of sizzling fajitas made with our Carne Asada Autentica
[sku 75977] and Fire Roasted Bell Peppers & Onions [sku 99437]. ¿ ey're phenomenal for rolling up and deep-
frying homemade ¿ autas with our Pulled Chicken Chili Verde [sku 76868]. We even ¿ nd that they make for a 
quick and easy, midday snack: simply warm them up a bit in a toaster oven or microwave, then apply a quick 
layer of butter and cracked black pepper or cinnamon sugar.

Flour Tortillas
tags: ["Alfresco Dining","Crack a Beer","Fire Up The Grill","Game Night","In Lieu of Pizza","Picnic","Put An Egg On It"]

title: Peach Raspberry Crisp
description:
Trader Joe's Pizza Seasoned Crackers are the mini, snackable version of pizza you didn't know you needed! 

Originating in Naples, pizza marinara is likely the oldest variety of tomato-topped pizza, and is the flavor profile 
we draw from for these unique Crackers. True to the source material, they're generously seasoned with the 
pizza marinara trinity of tangy tomatoes, aromatic oregano, and a kick of garlic. Thin, wheat-based Crackers 
stand in for pizza crust to facilitate satisfying crispiness, optimal snackability, and an uncanny resemblance to 
the real deal. 

To make the Crackers extra pizza-like, we recommend swinging by our cheese section and scooping up your 
cheese of choice-we're partial to All Natural Fresh Mozzarella Cheese [sku 077726]. Add cold cheese slices for 
a lighter feel, or melt them slightly for peak pizza replication. Pour a glass of Italian red wine (like Villa Cerrina 
Montepulciano D'Abruzzo [sku 048838]), or a pint of pilsner for elevated snackage during evening wind-downs 
and cozy gatherings with family and friends. Any way you slice it, Pizza Seasoned Crackers make for fun and 
flavorful munchies whenever you're feeling peckish!

Pizza Seasoned Crackers

title: Chocolate Brooklyn Babka
description:
Chocolate Brooklyn Babka is a sweet, swirly brioche-meets-cake loaf rooted in Eastern European Jewish 
traditions. In both Polish and Yiddish, "babka" is the diminutive of "baba," meaning "grandmother." And the 
character of this sweet, fluffy, chocolate-laden cake lives up to its namesake-welcoming you with open arms 
and old-world charm, just as your baba would. 

Trader Joe's Chocolate Brooklyn Babka is made for us by a small, kosher bakery in-where else?-Brooklyn, 
New York that literally grew out of their grandmother's kitchen. Following time-honored recipes and baking 
methods, they make a real babka's Babka. It doesn't get much better. 

Crafted from scratch in small batches, the sweet yeast dough is spread with a rich chocolate filling and twisted by 
hand before it goes into a high loaf pan to be proofed and baked.  The rich veins of chocolate reveal themselves 
as swirls when the Babka is sliced. Beautiful. Delicious!

For those Seinfeldians in the crowd, you know that a Babka will make you a "hero" at a dinner party. For those 
who never watched the sitcom, take our word for it-it's a sensational dessert, fully of dessert heroism. Of 
course, if you want to champion breakfast, it's a sure thing, too. Great with a cup of coffee or a glass of chilled 
milk, served warm or at room temperature, "You can't beat a Babka!" And you can't beat our price on Babkas, 
either. We're selling each 18-ounce, kosher-certified Chocolate Brooklyn Babka for $4.99. Find it with our 
other fresh-baked breads and cakes!

Detail of a Babka Slice

title: Carb Savvy Tortillas made with Whole Wheat
description:
If you are not that carb savvy, you might think 9g of carbohydrates in one serving of Trader Joe's Carb Savvy 
Tortillas is not that impressive. In fact, for someone watching their carbs, it's excellent! 

Carb Savvy Tortillas contain less overall carbs than regular tortillas, and the carbs they do contain are mostly 
from dietary fiber. Accordingly, these reduced-carb tortillas are an excellent source of dietary fiber, providing 
6g per tortilla. That's 21% of your daily recommended value of fiber! 

Enjoy them just as you would less-carb-savvy tortillas. Their smaller size is great for quesadillas, jumbo tacos, 
or even just for snacking. Find them every day on our bread shelves.

Carb Savvy Tortillas 
made with Whole Wheat
tags: ["Alfresco Dining","Cut The Mustard","Put An Egg On It","Rain or Shine"]

title: Lemon Flower Cookies
description:
"The flowers that bloom in the spring, tra la! Breathe promise of merry sunshine."
    -Gilbert & Sullivan

Ah, spring. That time of year when nature reawakens, spreading boundless blossoms across the landscape-it's 
downright inspiring. In fact, it's inspired us to celebrate the season the best way we know how: with jammy 
shortbread cookies. Trader Joe's Lemon Flower Cookies are made for us by a trusted bakery partner, who starts 
with a base of beautifully buttery shortbread dough that's been flavored with lemon oil and colored a pastel 
yellow with turmeric. After shaping the dough into a fancifully floral shape and baking it to a flawlessly crumbly 
texture, they then fill the center with a lemon jam, so that every bite sings with a satisfyingly citric sweetness.

We invite you to join us in giving a toast to springtime by enjoying a Trader Joe's Lemon Flower Cookie with 
a cup of your favorite tea-ideally, something similarly citric, like our always-excellent Organic Earl Grey [sku 
62680]. They make a handsome addition to a spring-themed dessert board, especially when you have folks over 
for brunch. And for a truly auspicious sweet treat, we recommend placing a Lemon Flower Cookie or two (or 
three) into a bowl of our Vanilla Ice Cream [sku 45883] swirled with our Authentic Lemon Curd [sku 07850].

Lemon Flower Cookies
tags: ["Alfresco Dining","Effortless Entertaining","Feeling Fancy","Giftable","Gild The Lily","Picnic","Treat Yourself"]

title: Ciabatta Baguette
description:
Ciabatta and baguette? Before now, you might have thought that ciabatta is ciabatta and a baguette is a baguette. 
But why can't we have the best of both worlds? What if ciabatta was a baguette? And this baguette had all the 
enchanting qualities of ciabatta? Cue Trader Joe's Ciabatta Baguette, the best of both bread worlds.

The loaf is in the shape of a baguette (meaning "wand" in Italian), but the bread itself is ciabatta bread. Ciabatta 
dough contains a higher moisture content than traditional baguette dough-over 70% in this case-giving it 
a thin, slightly caramelized crust and a light crumb with large holes. Better yet, it's made with just a few in-
gredients: unbleached wheat flour, water, sea salt, yeast, and malted barley. Though our supplier makes large 
quantities of bread, they are still able to achieve the sought-after artisanal taste and texture. And, really, what's 
more artisan than the uniting of two esteemed artisan breads?

Slice as you would a baguette and dip to your heart's content, preferably in Sicilian Selezione Extra Virgin Olive 
Oil [sku 78296] and Balsamic Vinegar of Modena [sku 58036]. It also makes an excellent panini. Or, go the 
traditional route: use it to soak up extra sauce from a heaping bowl of spaghetti-ciabatta is famous for its ability 
to be dipped without falling apart. For a bit more crunch, place the bread in a 400¿F oven for a few minutes.

Ciabatta Baguette
tags: ["Alfresco Dining","Cheese Board","Effortless Entertaining","Let's Bake!","Pair With Wine"]

title: Ciabatta Demi-Baguette
description:
Ciabatta and baguette? Before now, you might have thought that ciabatta is ciabatta and a baguette is a baguette.

Slice as you would a baguette of any size and dip to your heart's content, perhaps in Sicilian Selezione Extra

Ciabatta Demi-Baguette

title: Danish Princess Pastry
description:
When the weather heats up and turning on the oven loses its luster, you can still quell a craving for carbs 
with a visit to the bakery section at your neighborhood Trader Joe's. You'll find everyday staples like sliced 
breads, bagels, and tortillas, along with a seasonally rotating selection of muffins, cookies, and pastries-all for 
a fraction of the prices you might find elsewhere. Case in point: Trader Joe's Danish Princess Pastry.

Not to be confused with the Swedish sponge cake bearing the same name (who knew so many sweets were 
marked with this royal moniker?), Trader Joe's Danish Princess Pastry is made for us in Denmark, constructed 
of classic, tender pastry dough cradling a creamy, custard style, persipan-infused filling. (Fun fact: persipan is 
an aromatic confectionary ingredient used in baking, and as you might guess, akin to marzipan, but made with 
apricot kernels instead of almonds.) Rather than a single-serve round, this Danish is formed into an easy-to-
slice rectangle that can easily feed a crowd, and with a just-about-even ratio of pastry to filling, it's equally at 
home on a breakfast buffet or dessert platter. It can be enjoyed right out of the package, and if you can stand 
the heat, a 2-to-4-minute stint in the oven truly takes it over the top. Whether you enjoy your Pastry warm or 
cold, do as the Danes do and complement it with a strong, dark cup of coffee, like TJ's French Roast [sku 77083]. 

Danish Princess Pastry
tags: ["Alfresco Dining","Brunch All Day","Effortless Entertaining","Feeling Fancy","Gild The Lily","Stuff of Dreams"]

title: Sonora Style Flour Tortillas
description:
While many taquerias across the Americas tend to default to corn tortillas, Sonoran cuisine is famed for its use 
of flour-and if you've ever had a Sonora-style street taco, you'll know exactly why. Perfectly pliant in texture, 
and with a mild, just slightly sweet flavor, a warm, Sonora-style flour tortilla can be a true revelation when 
paired with the right protein. After carrying Mini Sonora Style Tortillas [sku 73586] in our West Coast stores for 
a few years, we felt the time was right to bring this celebrated tortilla style to all our stores, which is why we're 
introducing these larger-sized Trader Joe's Sonora Style Flour Tortillas nationally.

Prudently proportioned for making hearty, filling fajitas, or marvelously melty quesadillas, our Sonora Style 
Flour Tortillas are a must-have for making all your favorites within the Mexican and Tex Mex culinary canon. 
And since each package contains 12  Flour Tortillas, that leaves a lot of room for experimentation, whether 
you choose to go elegantly simple (like a mini burrito with beans, rice, and grilled Carne Asada [sku 75977]) or 
more complex (like a shrimp quesadilla with Jalapeño Monterey Jack Cheese [sku 09359] and blistered Shishito 
Peppers [sku 54173]).

Sonora Style Flour Tortillas

title: Cinnamon Twist Danish
description:
Nothing really beats a big, proper, multi-layered, custard-filled Danish. And Trader Joe's Cinnamon Twist 
Danish is a decidedly big and proper Danish-it even properly comes to us from Denmark! Each one is carefully 
crafted with meticulously laminated dough, which is layered with a creamy, cinnamon-spiced, custard-like 
filling, then twisted into a round spiral before being baked to a glorious golden brown. Deliciously sweet (but 
definitely not too sweet), each bite has a lovely note of sugar and cinnamon spice, making this proper Danish 
a properly magnificent way to start your morning.

A bit like a cross between a cinnamon bun and a classic breakfast pastry, our Cinnamon Twist Danish can be 
enjoyed as-is, right out of the box, or slightly warmed in the oven or toaster. When heated, its cinnamon bun 
similarities are most prominent: you get that rich, warm, ever-so-slightly gooey cinnamon sugar flavor, which 
provides a perfect foil to the texture of the mutli-layered pastry. Try bringing one, along with fresh coffee or 
tea, to your next morning meeting: you'll be most popular person there. And at the value we're offering for each 
box, you might even think about bringing two...

Cinnamon Twist Danish
tags: ["Brunch All Day","Effortless Entertaining","Family Style","Rise & Shine","Stuff of Dreams"]

title: Salted Caramel Swirl Danish
description:
Nothing really beats a proper, multi-layered, custard-filled Danish. And Trader Joe's Salted Caramel Swirl 
Danish is a decidedly proper Danish-it even properly comes to us from Denmark! Carefully crafted for us 
by a Danish bakery partner, each is one is made with meticulously laminated dough, which is then filled with 
almond cream and a delicately salted, caramel custard-style swirl, before being baked to a glorious golden 
brown. Deliciously sweet (but definitely not too sweet), each bite has an elegant mix of caramel and sea salt 
notes, with just a slight hint of marzipan, making it a properly magnificent way to start your morning.

Available to us for a limited time, our Salted Caramel Swirl Danish pairs particularly well with rich, robust 
coffees (like our Fair Trade Breakfast Blend [sku 74368]) and earthy, slightly citric teas (like our Organic Earl 
Grey [sku 62680]). It can be enjoyed right out of the box, at room temperature, or slightly warmed in the 
oven or toaster to provide a nice aromatic and textural boost to your eating experience. And since it's such a 
remarkable value, you can be the hero of your next social gathering by bringing a box or two along-all without 
breaking the bank.

Salted Caramel Swirl Danish

title: Glazed Chocolate Donut Holes
description:
Donuts are a surprisingly recent addition to the Trader Joe's bakery shelves, and with good reason: we had 
to find some that were tender, sweet, cakey, and moist enough to bear the Trader Joe's name. And while we 
eventually struck dough¿ er, gold with donuts of the Apple Cider [sku 64320] and Glazed Sour Cream [sku 
65569] varieties, our gluten free customers haven't had the opportunity to enjoy a TJ's donut-until now. 
Introducing Trader Joe's Glazed Chocolate Donut Holes!

Ticking those requisite boxes of tender, sweet, cakey, and moist, these rich, two-bite-sized Chocolate Donut 
Holes deliver everything you'd expect from a classic donut shop experience, right down to their shiny, sugary 
Glaze. Yet unlike the classic, they are dairy free and gluten free (the latter status earned thanks to a blend of 
tapioca starch, rice flour, and corn starch). Each package contains about 20 Donut Holes-more than enough 
to quell a donut craving or grant you "best coworker ever" status at your next breakfast meeting. But donut 
take our word for it (you didn't think we'd let that opportunity pass us by, did you?)-pick up a package at your 
neighborhood Trader Joe's and taste for yourself! You'll find them on our bakery shelves, every day.

Glazed Chocolate Donut Holes
tags: ["Alfresco Dining","Brunch All Day","Family Style","Finger Food","Midday Snacks","Rise & Shine","Treat Yourself"]

title: Organic Garlic Bread
description:
If garlic bread is the king of carbs (and we'd certainly argue that it has a legitimate claim to that throne), then 
it's time to prepare a royal engagement, because Trader Joe's Bake at Home Organic Garlic Bread is now 
available on our bakery shelves! Each hearty, rustic loaf comes pre-sliced, seasoned with a strikingly savory 
and herbaceous garlic Parmesan spread, and arrives in a vaccuum-sealed bag to ensure maximum freshness. 
Once home, all it takes is about 15 minutes in an oven pre-heated to 425°F (or atop a grill set to medium-high 
heat) before the crust becomes captivatingly crisp, the cheese spread turns marvelously melty, and the garlic 
grows alluringly aromatic.

While other ready-to-bake garlic breads tend to be on the softer side, Trader Joe's Bake at Home Organic 
Garlic Bread has a firm, chewy, almost ciabatta-like texture. In addition to helping hold the garlic Parmesan 
spread within its crumb structure exceptionally well, we find that this texture also makes it an even better 
accompaniment to soups and pastas. Try using a slice to sop up any extra sauce from our Spaghetti Carbornara 
[sku 75759] or Cajun Style Chicken Alfredo [sku 93370], and you'll see exactly what we mean. 

Bake at Home
Organic Garlic Bread
tags: ["Alfresco Dining","Crack a Beer","Dinner Hack","Family Style","Game Night","Let's Bake!","Pair With Wine","Picnic"]

title: Snickerdoodle Cookies
description:
Widely celebrated for their superlatively soft texture, sweet, cinnamon-y flavor, and exceedingly fun-to-say 
name, we're big fans of snickerdoodles here at Trader Joe's. So, when the time came to bring in our own version 
to our Bakery shelves, we knew we had to get every aspect of it right. That meant only the most satisfyingly 
crispy exterior, only the most pleasantly chewy interior, and only the most bright and flavorful cinnamon-
sugar coating would do-or, perhaps we should say, would snickerdoo. And wouldn't you know, the makers of 
our new Trader Joe's Snickerdoodle Cookies have snickerdone it!

Each box of Trader Joe's Snickerdoodle Cookies contains a dozen perfectly baked, scrumptiously cinammon-y 
Snickerdoodles, ready to be enjoyed whenever the Snickerdoodle mood strikes. (Please pardon the repetition; 
it really is just that fun to say.) Made from a traditional, homestyle recipe that includes cream of tartar for an 
extra crisp texture and korintje cinnamon for an even brighter touch of cinnamon spice in every bite, they 
make a great school or work lunch dessert, as well as a simple, anytime sweet treat. And we'd be remiss not to 
mention how fantastically well they function as the base for a seriously superb ice cream sandwich. 

Snickerdoodle Cookies

title: Brown Sugar Cardamom Buns
description:
Belonging to the same plant family that lays claim to ginger and turmeric, cardamom is a less well-known, 
yet just as versatile spice that lends pungent, peppery warmth, complex floral notes, and zesty hints of citrus 
to everything from baked goods to sauces to meatloaf. It's an especially prominent player in traditional 
Scandinavian pastries (which are currently experiencing a moment in the spotlight), and happens to play a 
starring role in our very own Trader Joe's Brown Sugar Cardamom Buns.

These limited-edition Sweet Rolled Danish Pastries are made in Denmark, where our supplier hand-forms 
the eggy dough into elegant knots, and incorporates plenty of Cardamom and Brown Sugar in the process. 
Once baked, the resulting pastry isn't overly sweet, allowing the heady spice notes to take center stage in each 
tender bite. Cozy up with a Bun and a cup of rich, dark roast coffee as an antidote to chilly winter weather-
they can be enjoyed right out of the package, or heated for a few minutes in the oven. Perhaps best of all, you 
can find packages of two, generously-sized Brown Sugar Cardamom Buns on the bakery shelves at your 
neighborhood Trader Joe's, for less than the price of one similar pastry elsewhere-if one can even be found!

Brown Sugar Cardamom Buns
tags: ["Brunch All Day","Gild The Lily","Rise & Shine","Stuff of Dreams"]

title: Organic Seeded Bread
description:
Bread. Even though modern diet culture tells us to fear it, bread is a scrumptiously inevitable household staple. 
Why shouldn't it be? It's delicious, filling, and in many cases, quite nutritious-and if you're a fan of all things 
delicious, filling, and nutritious, you might want to head to your local Trader Joe's, because we've got a new 
bread on the scene: Trader Joe's Organic Seeded Bread.

Made with organic wheat and whole wheat flour and sweetened with a touch of organic sugar cane molasses,  
Trader Joe's Organic Seeded Bread is soft, chewy, and ever-so-slightly sweet. Loaded with organic sunflower, 
flax, poppy, and sesame seeds, it's also as hearty as can be, with a perfectly toothsome, seedy texture. Use it for 
all of your sandwich-making needs, or toast and slather it with TJ's Cultured Salted Butter [sku 53720] and TJ's 
Raspberry Preserves [sku 87805]-it'll be a symphony of seeds!

We're selling each 16-ounce loaf of Trader Joe's Organic Seeded Bread for $3.49. You'll find it on the bread 
racks in our East Coast stores.

title: Organic Ancient Grain & Seed Bread
description:
As "traders on the culinary seas," we're well known for our great selection of unique and exotic products from 
around the world. But if you ask a regular Trader Joe's customer, they'll tell you that we're also the spot for high-
quality, affordable basics. Like our new, sliced Organic Ancient Grain & Seed Bread. 

We've certainly carried loaves of certified organic, sliced sandwich bread before, but we think this Organic 
Ancient Grain & Seed Bread is truly superior. It may be a fresh loaf, but it's made with some "ancient" grains-or 
grains that remain closer to their original form than most modern wheat varieties, like organic khorasan wheat, 
amaranth, and whole grain spelt flours. It's also jam-packed with seeds, like organic flax sees, organic sesame 
seeds, organic pumpkin seeds, organic poppy seeds, and more. It's wholesome. It's hearty. And it's delicious.

Use a couple of slices to make a classic turkey or tuna sandwich. Or, spread some Trader Joe's Almond Butter 
[sku 056995] and Organic Concord Grape Jelly [sku 095224] on a slice and fold it in half for a quick AB&J. It also 
makes for some wonderful breakfast toast-just pop it in the toaster and slather it with TJ's Cultured Butter [sku 
53720] and your favorite preserves.

In the name of fantastic, everyday value, we're offering each 20-ounce loaf of Trader Joe's Organic Multigrain 
Bread for $3.69. You'll find them on our bread racks.
tags: ["Cut The Mustard","Family Style","Picnic","Put An Egg On It"]

title: Almost Everything Bagels
description:
There are few ways to earn instant popularity around the office as effective as showing up to work with an armful 
of bagels. Bagels are the universal, Good morning; we're glad you're here. And when the bagel that kickstarts your 
day just happens to be a really good bagel, well, even better-you'll be glad you're there, too.

Trader Joe's Everything Bagels are really good bagels, made for us using quality ingredients and without the 
use of artificial preservatives or dough conditioners. The secret to their bagel excellency is their baking process. 
First, the dough is proofed in high humidity and then set out to slowly ferment, which brings out all of the 
dough's delicious, subtle flavors. Next, the bagels are steamed to lock in that chewy center and create that perfect 
"skin." Then, they're off to the oven to be baked until they've acquired that perfect, golden-brown bagel crust. 
Finally, they're hand-rolled in an "everything" blend of sesame seeds, poppy seeds, minced garlic, and minced 
onion. Perfection.

Toast your Bagel and butter it up with our salted Cultured Butter [sku 53720]. Or, if you prefer, slather it with 
Cream Cheese [sku 12491] and sprinkle it with Everything But The Bagel Seasoning [sku 59137]. That's a whole lot 
of Everything! Your Bagel is a blank canvas; let your carbohydrate-saturated imagination run wild. 

You'll find Trader Joe's Everything Bagels in our bakery section, and we're selling each 22-ounce bag of six 
Bagels for $2.69. Be a mensch and buy a bunch! We've shopped around, and we know you won't find a price this 
low at your local bagel shop.

title: Everything Bagels
description:
These Bagels are everything! And by that, we mean Trader Joe's Everything Bagels are really excellent bagels, 
made for us by skilled bagel bakers using only quality ingredients. Of course, the secret to their bagel excellency 
rests firmly in the baking process and the attention to detail in every step. Since we use local bakeries, this 
baking process varies from region to region-nevertheless, you'll find every iteration to be wonderfully doughy 
inside, with a good chew on the outside.

These Bagels are also Everything because they're topped with traditional Everything seasonings, including 
sesame seeds, poppy seeds, garlic, onion, and salt. This means they are great when simply toasted with butter 
or cream cheese. But don't be afraid to add to 'the Everything'¿ Make an Everything Bagel pizza. Top with 
some Smoked Salmon [sku 13059]. You can even add Everything But the Bagel Seasoning [sku 59137]¿ so meta. 

You'll find Trader Joe's Everything Bagels in our bakery section; we're selling each 18-ounce bag of six for 
$1.99 to $2.69 (varies regionally)*.  

 *Please check QIL to confirm current pricing.

Everything Bagels

title: Plain Bagels
description:
We decided to change our bagels from a 4 oz bagel to a 3 oz.  size, which is the size 
we have in some other regions.  These have less carbs, less calories, yet work just 
as well as the larger bagels as a breakfast bread or sandwich (or pizza!). 
 
We're selling each 18 oz package of six Bagel Josef's Plain and Onion Bagels for 
$1.79.  
 
We're selling each 18 oz package of six Bagel Josef's Sprouted Bagels (Wheat, 
Sesame, and Cinnamon Raisin) for $1.99.

title: Cinnamon Raisin Bagels
description:
Cinnamon Raisin Bagels
Cinnamon Raisin Bagels are one of the top bagel flavors in 
supermarkets.  Ours are all natural, with no dough conditioners, 
and good cinnamon flavor, with moist plump raisins throughout. 

Great as an on-the-go breakfast, slathered with cream cheese or 
butter, toasted or not!  Also good as a sandwich "roll", for deli 
turkey or ham, maybe with a chutney spread. 

Opens for 1st orders on October 8, 2012.

title: Cinnamon Swirl Raisin Bagels
description:
There are few more effective ways to earn instant popularity than to show up at the office with an armful of 
bagels in the morning. Bagels just offer up that universal "good morning; we're glad you're here" vibe. And when 
the bagel that kickstarts your day just happens to be a really good bagel, well, even better.
 
Luckily, Trader Joe's Cinnamon Swirl Raisin Bagels are really good bagels. The secret to their bagel excellency 
is in the baking process. First, the cinnamon-y, raisin-studded dough is proofed and set out to ferment, which 
brings out all of its delicious, subtle flavors. Next, the bagels are kettle-boiled, which locks in a chewy center 
and creates that perfect bagel "skin." Then finally, they're off to the oven to be hearth-baked until they've 
acquired that perfect, golden-brown bagel crust.
 
Toast your Bagel and butter it up with TJ's Cultured Butter [sku 53720]. Or, if you prefer, slather it with TJ's 
Cream Cheese [sku 12491], then sprinkle it with cinnamon and sugar to really play up the Cinnamon Swirl. 
Your Bagel is a blank canvas; let your carbohydrate-saturated imagination run wild!

You'll find Trader Joe's Cinnamon Swirl Raisin Bagels in our bakery section, where we're selling each 18-ounce 
bag of six Bagels for $2.49.* Be a mensch and buy a bunch! We've shopped around, and we know you won't find 
a price this low at your local bagel shop. 

 *Please check QIL to confirm current pricing.

Cinnamon Swirl Raisin Bagels

title: Petit Fours Mousse Cakes
description:
In the 18th century, baking was a slightly more involved process than it is today. Back then, French bakers 
relied on ovens that took quite a long time to heat up, and even longer to cool down. So, after they were done 
making their breads for the day à grand fours ("at large oven," i.e., at full heat), they would take the opportunity 
to use their oven's residual heat to bake small, delicate pastries à petit fours ("at small oven," i.e., at diminishing 
heat). Though ovens have changed over the years, the fandom for petit fours cakes has only grown. We're 
certainly fans, which is precisely why we're introducing Trader Joe's Petit Fours Mousse Cakes to our bakery 
tables for the holidays.

Each package contains nine elegantly decorated, two-or-three-bite-sized Petit Fours Cakes in three distinct 
styles: three rich chocolate Cakes layered with silky chocolate Mousse, covered in a dark chocolatey coating; 
three vanilla Cakes layered with velvety vanilla Mousse, covered in a sweet vanilla coating and topped with 
pearl sugar; and three chocolate Cakes layered with smooth coffee Mousse, covered in a mocha coating and 
topped with bits of dark chocolate and sugar. Ideal for serving at holiday parties and get-togethers of all kinds, 
these light, sweet, and texturally refined Petit Fours Mousse Cakes make a great inclusion for a dessert table, 
a lovely host or hostess gift when visiting friends or family, and a delightfully decorative addition to an after-
dinner pie or cake plate after a holiday feast.

Petit Fours Mousse Cakes

title: Vegan Gingerbread Loaf
description:
Did you know? Some of the first recipes for gingerbread originated in Ancient Greece, over 2,000 years ago. 
These early versions were a little closer to honey-sweetened flatbreads than the pastry we know today, and they 
hardly had the architectural utility we currently enjoy in our Gingerbread House Kits [sku 11692], but the point 
remains: for millennia, people have known that good things happen when you bake ginger into your bread. 
This year, we reached out to a baker who knows this all too well, and knows how to do so without the use of 
any animal-based products. Once we had a chance to try it, we promptly made the decision to bring into our 
stores. And thus, Trader Joe's Vegan Gingerbread Loaf was born.

This Loaf has everything you'd want in a holiday gingerbread, like rich brown sugar, hearty molasses, and 
invigorating ginger. You can slice it and serve it right out of the package with a nice hot drink, like our Wintry 
Blend Coffee [sku 81829], or, if you're willing to go the extra mile, give it a quick toast and spread it with your 
favorite vegan butter or cream cheese. Mmm. For as long as we can keep it in stock, we're selling 15-ounce 
Trader Joe's Vegan Gingerbread Loaves for $4.29* each. Look for them in our bakery section. 

 *Please check QIL to confirm current pricing.

Vegan Gingerbread Loaf
tags: ["Gild The Lily","Merry-making","Rain or Shine","Rise & Shine","Treat Yourself","Welcoming"]

title: Olive Fougasse
description:
Etymologically derived from the same root word as focaccia, a fougasse is a traditional style of bread originating 
from southeastern France. Combining the satisfyingly chewy crumb structure of an Italian focaccia with the 
signature flair of French baking, fougasses where often just as practical as they were palatable, way back when: 
prior to the widespread use of thermometers, some bakers would use the time it took to fully cook a fougasse 
to determine how hot an oven was. Now, we can't speak to the temperature measuring abilities of Trader Joe's 
Olive Fougasse, the latest addition to our bakery section, but we can tell you that its crisp, delicious crust, light, 
airy interior, and generously distributed slices of Kalamata and black olives make for one seriously delicious, 
anytime bread.

Made in a fetching, four-sectioned design, which can be easily torn or cut into individual servings, our Olive 
Fougasse makes an excellent accompaniment to practically any meal. It can be served entirely on its own or 
with a bit of butter for spreading or olive oil for dipping, and can even be enjoyed as an especially flavorful 
bread for sandwiches. For an even crispier crust, we suggest giving it 3-4 minutes in the oven at 400°F, just 
prior to serving.

Olive Fougasse

title: Pecan Pie
description:
The pecan, like other members of the hickory genus, is not truly a nut, but is technically a drupe, a fruit with a 
single stone or pit, surrounded by a husk. The seed inside the husk is the rich, buttery "nut" that we consume, 
with great delight. Its name is a Native American word of Algonquin origin, and while the jury is still out on 
correct pronunciation (pe-CAN, PEE-can or puh-KAN, just to name a few), we think most would agree that the 
noblest use of the pecan is in the making of a classic Southern dessert, the Pecan Pie.

Trader Joe's Pecan Pie is an indulgent nod to culinary tradition. The custard base with butter and brown sugar 
is decidedly sweet, with notes of vanilla. Its soft, melt-in-your-mouth texture is the ideal counterpoint to the 
generous amounts of crunchy, buttery pecans added to each batch. The pie is baked just until set, creating a 
crispy outer crust and a gooey, caramelized center. Try it with Vanilla [sku 45883] or Chocolate Ice Cream [sku 
78572] for dessert (add a drizzle of chocolate syrup just before serving to double down on the decadence), or 
with a freshly brewed cup of French Vanilla Coffee [sku 51484] for a Saturday morning treat.

Pecan Pie

title: Raspberry Croissant Carré
description:
Made for us in California by the best boulangers we've found this side of the Atlantic, Trader Joe's Raspberry 
Croissant Carré starts, as all good things do, with a classic laminated dough (a.k.a. dough that's been repeatedly 
folded with layers of butter to create the flaky Croissant eating experience). The dough is paired with a tart 
Raspberry filling that's been sweetened with a bit of sugar and complemented with a touch of lemon juice to 
further amplify the fruit. But rather than rolling them into the classic Croissant shape, the layers of dough 
are sandwiched around the jammy filling, like a coffee cake-a sedimentary construction that allows for the 
inclusion of much more filling than you'd find in an individual croissant. Merveilleux!

Sprinkled with coarse sugar crystals and baked until the dough reaches a lovely, deep golden hue, this impressive 
Carré (that's French for "square," a nod to this pastry's squarish shape) serves six. Pick one up from the bakery 
shelf at your neighborhood Trader Joe's and enjoy right out of the package-it's a fantastic slice-and-serve 
option for a breakfast meeting or weekend brunch, paired with a steaming cup of coffee. To attain maximum 
deliciousness, remove the outer packaging and warm the Carré in a 350°F oven-you'll be rewarded with a 
fresh, French-style pastry, without the upscale bakery price tag you might find elsewhere. Bon appétit!

Raspberry Croissant Carré
tags: ["Alfresco Dining","Brunch All Day","Effortless Entertaining","Feeling Fancy","Rise & Shine","Treat Yourself"]

title: Chocolate Dipped Danish Cookies
description:
From spectacular pies to magical muffins and everything in between, the bakery section at your neighborhood 
Trader Joe's is a veritable treasure trove of treats, especially during the holiday season. New to our holiday lineup 
this year are Trader Joe's Chocolate Dipped Danish Cookies, made for us in-where else?-Denmark! Peek 
into the window of their upscale, bakery-style box, and you'll discover an equally fancy assortment of Danish 
Cookies: Marzipan Napoleon Hats, tender cookies filled with sweet, almond marzipan; Almond Triangles, 
made with a short crust base, an almond filling, and topped with sliced almonds; and classic, chewy Coconut 
Macaroons. And for good measure, the bottom of each Cookie is Dipped in rich Chocolate. Yum.

You probably don't need instructions for enjoying these delightful Danish Cookies, but we will say they pair 
famously with a strong cuppa, morning, afternoon, or night. For a very limited time, you'll find Chocolate 
Dipped Danish Cookies in the bakery section at your neighborhood TJ's, for a fraction of the price you'd pay 
at a Danish bakery (or a plane ticket to Denmark, for that matter).

Chocolate Dipped Danish Cookies

title: Ciabatta Rolls
description:
Not so very long ago, in 1982, a man in Verona, Italy invented ciabatta bread. He decided the loaf looked 
quite like his wife's slippers (the English translation of ciabatta), and so bread named after footwear was born. 
Even more recently, we decided to start selling such bread, like Trader Joe's Ciabatta Rolls (even though 
these are more like miniature slippers).

Ciabatta dough contains a high moisture content-over 70% in this case-giving it a thin, slightly caramel-
ized crust and a light crumb with large holes. Better yet, it's made with just a few ingredients: unbleached 
wheat flour, water, sea salt, yeast, and malted barley. Though our supplier makes large quantities of bread, 
they are still able to achieve the sought-after artisanal taste and texture. And, really, what's more artisan than 
miniature versions of an esteemed artisan bread?

Dip these tasty rolls to your heart's content, perhaps in Sicilian Selezione Extra Virgin Olive Oil [sku 78296] 
and Balsamic Vinegar of Modena [sku 58036]. Make little panini sandwiches with mozzarella, tomatoes, and 
basil. Or, go the traditional route: use it to soak up extra sauce after a heaping bowl of spaghetti-ciabatta is 
famous for its ability to be dipped without falling apart. For a crispy crust, place the bread in a 400¿F oven for 
a few minutes.

Ciabatta Rolls
tags: ["Alfresco Dining","Cut The Mustard","Pair With Wine","Put An Egg On It","Rain or Shine"]

title: Teeny Tiny Apple Pies
description:
The appeal of a freshly baked apple pie is undeniable. The making of said pie, however, with its finicky crust 
composition and long bake time (not to mention its large-serving format), often creates a roadblock to its 
enjoyment. Thankfully, sidestepping the prep and skipping straight to the eating is not a pie-in-the-sky plan-
it's actually quite possible with a trip to your neighborhood Trader Joe's and a box of Teeny Tiny Apple Pies.

Trader Joe's Teeny Tiny Apple Pies are made for us in Canada using sweet-tart, exceptionally juicy Northern 
Spy apples. Nestled in a flaky, buttery crust, the cinnamon-spiced, diced apple filling is topped with a brown 
sugar crumble and baked to a golden brown. The finished Pies are packed four to a box, each measuring 
about three inches in diameter, so you can enjoy their sweet, tender, apple-y goodness whenever a craving for 
pie presents itself-no fork or pie server required. (Think "apple pie cookie" and you're on the right track.) 
Alternatively, you could warm a Pie in the microwave or air fryer and serve it alongside a cup of Organic Fair 
Trade Breakfast Blend Coffee [sku 95142]. Or for a presentation that's sure to have you pie-eyed, go full à la 
mode and gild one with a scoop of Super Premium French Vanilla Ice Cream [sku 45883] and a flourish of Fleur 
de Sel Caramel Sauce [sku 95214]. 

Teeny Tiny Apple Pies
tags: ["Date Night","Fall Faves","Family Style","Finger Food","Stuff of Dreams","Treat Yourself"]

title: Pumpkin Brioche Twist
description:
Trader Joe's Customers love our Sliced French Brioche [sku 56582]. This buttery, moist, and perfectly French 
braided bread is utterly appealing. With the holidays upon us, we thought, why not tweak the recipe a bit and 
come up with a pumpkin-y version. That could only be more appealing, right?!

Our supplier spent some quality time researching how to combine that brioche texture with the taste of smooth 
pumpkin for this Pumpkin Brioche Twist. Their time was well worth it-proved with one bite of the milky, 
soft-textured crumb and its pumpkin-tinged flavor. This holiday pumpkin profile is made complete by a swirl 
of pumpkin pie spices, which include cinnamon, ginger, and nutmeg.

A piece of this pre-sliced bread is seriously satisfying as-is, right out of the package. But we would be remiss 
if we didn't mention how amazing a lightly toasted, generously buttered piece tastes. Pumpkin Heaven! Find 
Trader Joe's 16.8-ounce Pumpkin Brioche Twist in our bakery section, and please note: it's only available for 
a limited time, while supplies last.

 *Please check QIL to confirm current pricing.

Pumpkin Brioche Twist
tags: ["Fall Faves","Feeling Fancy","Put An Egg On It","Rise & Shine"]

title: Apple Cinnamon Buns
description:
There are folks that are, naturally, morning people. And then there are those that, despite all efforts, are 
emphatically not. While we've never quite figured out the trick to complete morning person conversion, 
we've certainly found something that helps: a flaky, perfectly-baked morning pastry, like a Trader Joe's Apple 
Cinnamon Bun. These Danish-style pastries are made for us by (appropriately enough) a bakery partner in 
Denmark, who crafts each Bun by twisting sweet, cinnamon-apple-compote-filled dough into a quick knot, 
topping it with a light, streusel-like crumb, then baking it until it's gloriously golden brown. It's enough to make 
anyone aspire to morning person-hood.

While our Apple Cinnamon Buns can be enjoyed at room temperature, right out of the box, we find they reach 
new heights of texture, aroma, and flavor when lightly toasted just before serving. Similarly, while they can 
be eaten solo, they're especially delectable when served with a nice cup of tea or coffee, like our Organic Fair 
Trade Breakfast Blend [sku 95142]. Regardless of where you fall on the morning person spectrum, our Apple 
Cinnamon Buns are sure to delight-and their value is a real eye-opener, too.

Apple Cinnamon Buns
tags: ["Brunch All Day","Fall Faves","Feeling Fancy","Rise & Shine","Stuff of Dreams"]

title: Gluten Free Cinnamon Raisin Bread
description:
As a snack, a simple slice of Cinnamon Raisin Bread approaches perfection. The sweet raisins and aromatic 
cinnamon make it seem like a special baked treat, one that's elevated even further by a simple warm up in the 
toaster. And yet, it's just a bit of bread-not a donut or a slice of cake-so it never quite corsses the line into 
"dessert" territory!

We want all our customers to have the Cinnamon Raisin Bread experience, and that's why we're bringing 
Trader Joe's Gluten Free Cinnamon Raisin Bread back to our bakery shelves. Reformulated with a new recipe 
that no longer includes eggs (which means it's now also vegan!), this hearty loaf smells and tastes just like 
classic Cinnamon Raisin Bread-because it is! All we've done is replaced the wheat flour with a combination 
of brown rice flour and tapioca flour. Husked brown rice is finely ground and used as the primary substitute for 
wheat flour. The tapioca flour-derived from the root of the cassava plant from South America-helps provide 
some of the crispness and chew that's often missing in other gluten free breads.

This bread is great for breakfast, toasted with a spread of butter (or a bit of Trader Joe's Vegan Buttery Spread 
[sku 71782], to keep it totally vegan). Of course, it's also great with a variety of fruit or nut spreads, or try it 
egg-battered and pan-fried for a delicious French toast.

Gluten Free Cinnamon Raisin Bread
tags: ["Brunch All Day","Family Style","Rain or Shine","Rise & Shine"]

title: Sourdough Sandwich Bread
description:
Toast sounds simple, and in a way, it is simple. But, when you consider that the source of good toast is really good 
bread, it suddenly sounds not so simple after all. After testing a wide variety of contenders, we've come to the 
unanimous decision that the very best bread for toast-making is sourdough. And because toast requires slices 
of bread, our conclusion also included the rationale that sliced Sourdough is the most practical Sourdough for 
this particular endeavor. And thus, Trader Joe's Sourdough Sandwich Bread tops our list of "Best Breads for 
Toast" for this and every year.

Our Sourdough Sandwich Bread is made exclusively for us, and will be slightly different depending on where 
in Trader Joe's country you pick up your loaf - the flavor of Sourdough depends largely on the "starter," which 
is a living culture that lends the bread its signature sour profile. Because every starter is different, every bakery 
produces a slightly different flavor profile. What they all have in common is their excellence - especially when 
toasted. So slather on some butter, a bit of jam, or make a PB&J on Sourdough toast. You may even take that 
toasting to a higher level, and make a scrumptious grilled cheese... on Sourdough. Toast away. You'll be glad 
you did.

We're selling each 24-ounce loaf of Trader Joe's Sourdough Sandwich Bread for $2.99, every day. You'll find 
it on our bakery racks.
tags: ["Backpack Ready","Cut The Mustard","Family Style","Picnic","Put An Egg On It","Rise & Shine"]

title: Hand Twisted Cinnamon Sugar Bread
description:
.While we seriously doubt we'll need to twist your arm to convince you to try Trader Joe's Hand Twisted 
Cinnamon Sugar Bread, we're going to tout its tastiness anyway, because-truthfully-we're twitterpated!

Our Cinnamon Sugar Bread is fluffy-yet-dense, sweet-but-not-too-sweet, and smoothly & superbly 
cinnamony. (The cinnamon flavor runs high, but since our supplier uses korintje cinnamon, it's a bit less 
"nippy" than other cinnamon varietals.) And here's the plot twist: each loaf is actually made up of three separate 
pieces of dough, rolled in cinnamon & sugar, then Hand Twisted together. It's terrific toasted and, boy, does it 
make a fine French toast... and we've purposefully left it unsliced, so you can slice the bread to fit the breakfast! 
(Or lunch, snack, etc., etc.)

Hand Twisted Cinnamon Sugar Bread
tags: ["Alfresco Dining","Brunch All Day","Family Style","Rain or Shine","Rise & Shine","Welcoming"]

title: Whole Wheat English Muffins
description:
If you ever order an English Muffin in England, you'll likely get a funny look:  Like the "French" in "French 
fries," the "English" in "English muffin" is just an American moniker, mostly assigned to distinguish the bearer 
of said moniker from traditional, American-style muffins. (You know, the kind that come sitting in little paper 
wrappers¿and are often quite sweet.)

Trader Joe's Whole Wheat English Muffins are not sweet muffins-if anything, they're a bit savory. Technically 
speaking, they're soft, slightly spongy (picture a sourdough-like texture), puck-shaped pieces of bread, 
horizontally bisected into two, equal, circular halves. Each Muffin has a toothsome exterior (more of a "skin" 
than a "crust," though), and an interior filled with plenty of¿well, least we infringe upon on any trademarks, 
we'll say they're filled with plenty of "pockets & crevices." Yes, that's it. Pockets & crevices¿ All of which is to 
say, our new, kaizen-ed English Muffins are hearty and delicious-perfect for toasting and slathering with butter, 
cream cheese, peanut butter, etc. or for using as the base of a breakfast sandwich.

Whole Wheat English Muffins
tags: ["Brunch All Day","Put An Egg On It","Rise & Shine"]

title: Gluten Free Multigrain Bread
description:
TJ's Gluten-Free Multigrain Bread is made for us by a family-owned and operated bakery in a dedicated 
gluten-free facility using a special blend of brown rice, whole grain sorghum, amaranth, millet, and teff flours-
as well as sprouted millet, brown rice, and oats. In addition to providing an impressive two grams of fiber and 
three grams of protein per two-slice serving, this mix makes the bread soft and flavorful, instead of tough or 
grainy. In fact, we specifically chose this bread to appeal to non-gluten-free customers just as much as the 
gluten-free crowd. Because when it comes to bread, you shouldn't have to compromise.

We recommend toasting a few slices until nicely browned, then piling them high with your favorite deli meat 
and condiments, with a crisp Organic Kosher Dill Pickle Spear [sku 54867]. Or, take advantage of this bread's 
hearty nature and combine Crunchy Salted Almond Butter [sku 52293] with Fresh Raspberry Preserves [sku 
87805] for an uncommonly delicious PB&J-that just happens to be gluten-free, too!

 *Please check QIL to confirm current pricing.

Gluten Free Multigrain Bread with Sprouted 
Ancient Grains
tags: ["Alfresco Dining","Brunch All Day","Cut The Mustard","Picnic","Put An Egg On It","Rise & Shine","The \"X\" Factor"]

title: Gluten Free Madeleine Cookies
description:
The Madeleine is a truly exceptional cookie-so exceptional, in fact, that the broader baking world considers 
it to be, technically, a small cake. If you've ever tried a Madeleine, that might not come as a surprise, as their 
mildly sweet flavor and soft, airy crumb are certainly as luxurious as any cake you'll find. That's especially true 
of Trader Joe's Gluten Free Madeleine Cookies, made for us by a bakery partner in France who uses just 
the right ratio of gluten free flours and starches to give each of these Madeleines the same superb flavor and 
captivatingly cake-like texture as you'd expect from their conventional counterparts at a Parisian patisserie. 
Talk about having your cake and eating it, too!

While our Gluten Free Madeleine Cookies can be enjoyed entirely on their own, as a solitary sweet treat 
or quick, post-meal dessert, we're particularly partial to serving them with a cup of coffee or tea. (Try them 
dunked in our French Roast [sku 57359] for an especially appropriate accompaniment.) And for an even more 
elevated eating experience (and a romantic dessert-for-two option), try dipping them in melted dark chocolate 
and sprinkling them with chopped Pistachios [sku 98684] or crushed Freeze Dried Strawberries [sku 80665].

Gluten Free Madeleine Cookies

title: BREAD CINNAMON RAISIN SLICED
description:
We're not the types to say this kind of thing cavalierly, so believe us when we say that we may have found the 
greatest thing since sliced bread: Trader Joe's Sliced Cinnamon Raisin Bread! Made for us by a trusted bakery 
partner, each loaf contains a sweet, faintly spicy swirl of cinnamon sugar, and is studded with juicy, ever-so-
slightly tart raisins throughout. Once baked, our supplier cuts the loaf into thin, easy-to-portion slices that can 
be enjoyed for their super soft texture as-is, right out of the package, or toasted until they're lightly browned 
and satisfyingly crisp.

Sweet, cinnamon-y, and punctuated with occasional pops of flavor from the rich, juicy raisins, Trader Joe's 
Sliced Cinnamon Raisin Bread is sure to bring a bravura performance to the breakfast table. It serves 
excellently as a simple slice of toast, with a bit of butter or your favorite non-dairy spread. It's great for making 
thin and crisp slices of French toast that pair especially well with warm Maple Syrup [sku 04892] and Organic 
Powdered Sugar [sku 59227]. And for an intriguing mix of savory and sweet, try it as a sandwich bread with 
bacon, a fried egg, and a crispy Hashbrown [sku 94769] patty.

Sliced Cinnamon Raisin Bread

title: Gluten Free Strawberry Muffins
description:
Like our everyday Gluten Free Double Chocolate Muffins [sku 74110], Trader Joe's Gluten Free Strawberry 
Muffins combine a gluten free flour blend (including white and brown rice flours, potato starch, and tapioca 
starch) with sweet cream buttermilk and sour cream to create one of the most marvelously moist muffins 
we've ever tasted, gluten free or otherwise. This seasonal Strawberry spin, however, trades the aforementioned 
chocolate for a warm vanilla and brown sugar-infused Muffin base, emboldened with plenty of sweet 
strawberries in every bite! 

This artful amalgamation of bright Strawberry flavor and moist Muffin-y goodness makes for a terrific on-
the-go breakfast alongside a hot cup of TJ's French Vanilla Coffee [sku 51484]. It also makes for a splendid end 
to your evening served à la mode, courtesy of a scoop of TJ's Super Premium French Vanilla Ice Cream [sku 
78576]. Pick up a package while you can-like summer berry season, these Gluten Free Strawberry Muffins 
will only be around for a limited time!

Gluten Free Strawberry Muffins

title: Mini Chocolate Mousse Flowers
description:
We all know April showers bring May flowers¿but did you also know they bring Trader Joe's Mini Chocolate 
Mousse Flowers?! Nearly as beautiful-and most definitely tastier-than their botanical counterparts, these 
treats only pop up on our bakery shelves around this time of year, but, man, is the season sweet. 

First, we start with a layer of moist chocolate cake. A light, fluffy chocolate mousse comes next. Then, these two 
layers are coated in a sweet white chocolate that's been colored using turmeric powder and beet juice extract 
to give these blooms their bright yellow and pink colors. And that floral shape doesn't just happen by magic: a 
special water jet cutting technology is used to slice ever-so-perfect petals.

Because our Mini Chocolate Mousse Flowers are mini, they're perfect for sharing a package between friends. 
Enjoy one with TJ's French Vanilla Ice Cream [sku 78576], or have one to brighten up a lingering rainy after-
noon.

Grab a bouquet of six Trader Joe's Mini Chocolate Mousse Flowers (a 4.5-ounce package) for $2.99, and only 
for a limited time. The next time you'll see these cakes, they'll be round and suspiciously gourd-like...

05.15.
17

title: Peanut Butter Brookie
description:
A few years ago, we introduced a baked treat that dared to ask, "if you love brownies, and you love chocolate 
chip cookies, why not enjoy both at the same time?". The Brookie [sku 61281] was an instant hit, and its dual-
layered approach to dessert continues to be a consummate customer favorite to this day. So much so, in fact, 
that we felt the time was right to bring in another delectable doubleheader onto our shelves. Made for us by 
the same supplier as the adored original, Trader Joe's Peanut Butter Brookie takes the Brookie formula into 
a wonderfully nutty new direction.

To make each Peanut Butter Brookie, our supplier starts with a layer of rich, fudgy brownie batter, then tops 
it with a layer of sweet peanut butter cookie batter, complete with crunchy bits of chopped peanuts. After 
baking, they top it off with a sprinkle of sea salt to really round out that crunchy, salted peanut butter profile. 
With every bite, you get the classic flavor combo of chocolate and peanut butter, plus the extra dimension of a 
satisfyingly soft, just done cookie-brownie texture. Enjoy this Peanut Butter Brookie as an anytime sweet treat,  
straight out of the package, or, for something a little more involved, we're especially fond of it warmed up and 
topped with a scoop of ice cream...

Peanut Butter Brookie

title: Blueberry & Lemon Hand PIes
description:
When it comes to pies, bold fruit flavors and buttery, flaky crusts go hand in hand. And in Trader Joe's 
Blueberry & Lemon Hand Pies, you'll find both-handily! Made for us by the same brilliant bakery partners 
behind our fall-seasonal Apple Pumpkin Hand Pies [sku 74773], each bite of these hearty, hand-hold-able Pies 
is bursting with fresh blueberry (it's the first ingredient listed, in fact!) and sweet-tart sugared lemon, supported 
by an expertly crafted all-butter crust.  

Just as the name implies, Trader Joe's Blueberry & Lemon Hand Pies can easily be eaten sans knife and fork, 
making them an excellent option for packing along on picnics, adding to school or work lunches, or simply 
just enjoying on the go. That said, for those who prefer a slightly more involved experience, warming them up 
for a few minutes in the oven or air fryer will definitely be worth your while-especially with the addition of a 
dollop of whipped cream or scoop of your favorite ice cream. Just be sure to pick them up while we still have 
them on hand, because they're only available during the spring!

Blueberry & Lemon Hand Pies

title: Cheddar Jalapeño Pull Apart Bread
description:
If you'll allow us a moment of potential over-earnestness, there really is something magical about the act of enjoying 
a meal with folks that you love. It's a shared moment in every sense of the word: you're sharing time and space in 
addition to sharing nourishment. So when we find a food that brings the idea of sharing to the fore, as our tear-
and-share Cheddar Jalapeño Pull Apart Bread does, it holds a special place in our hearts. Call us romantics if you 
must-just don't call us late to the dinner table.

To make Trader Joe's Cheddar Jalapeño Pull Apart Bread, our supplier makes a fluffy, airy, almost focaccia-like 
dough, sprinkles it generously with shredded cheddar and sliced jalapeño peppers, then chops it into roll-sized 
pieces. After that, they cobble the pieces together in a tray and bake them just enough for you to finish the job at 
home. Out of your oven, the bread becomes delightfully warm, the cheese wonderfully gooey, and the jalapeños 
satisfyingly crisp. From there, you and anyone else you're sharing a meal with are free to pull the pieces apart and 
enjoy-together. It makes an excellent appetizer option, especially when combined with a fun dipping sauce like our 
Organic Ranch Dressing [sku 56051], and a delightfully spicy dinner roll option, too.

Cheddar Jalapeño Pull Apart Bread
tags: ["Alfresco Dining","Cold Front","Crack a Beer","Family Style","Picnic","Rain or Shine"]

title: Mini Chocolate Mousse Presents
description:
Back in 2015, we introduced a pastry that was set to be come somewhat of a phenomenon in our bakery section: 
seasonal Chocolate Mousse Eggs [sku 54742]. Our tasting panel loved these little eggs-thick layers of moist, 
rich chocolate cake topped with silky chocolate mousse and enrobed in Belgian chocolate-and as it would 
turn out, so did our customers. So, we thought, Why limit these mini Mousse cakes to just one season? Enter 
fall-focused Chocolate Mousse Pumpkins [sku 55381], and holiday-themed Mini Chocolate Mousse Trees [sku 
57283], also a big hits with our customers. 

This holiday season, though, we're replacing the Trees with Presents. They're the same high-quality mousse cakes 
you love (some say they taste like an upscale version of a certain individually-wrapped, American convenience 
store classic), shaped like perfect little rectangles and all tied-up with a white chocolate "ribbon" and "bow." 

The dictionary defines a presents as "things given to someone as gifts," and Trader Joe's Mini Chocolate Mousse 
Presents are the perfect gift for anyone you're sweet on. In the spirit of the season, we suggest picking up a 
package or two (or three, or four, or five...) to share with your friends and family; partners and pals; colleagues 
and countrymen. We're selling each 6-present, 5-ounce tray for $2.99. At less than fifty cents a Present, this 
might be the least expensive gift you'll give all year! You'll find Mini Chocolate Mousse Presents on our bakery 
tables, while the season is upon us. 

11.13
.17
